flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
Chinchou blink their shining antennae at one
another to claim their respective turf.
flavor_text_entries.gold:
It shoots positive
and negative elec­
tricity between the tips of its
two antennae and
zaps its enemies.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
On the dark ocean
floor, its only
means of communi­ cation is its
constantly flash­
ing lights.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
Its antennae, whi­
ch evolved from a
fin, have both po­ sitive and neg­
ative charges flo­
wing through them.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
CHINCHOU lets loose positive and
negative electrical charges from its
two antennas to make its prey faint. This POKéMON flashes its electric
lights to exchange signals with others.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
CHINCHOU’s two antennas are filled with
cells that generate strong electricity.
This POKéMON’s cells create so much electrical power, it even makes itself
tingle slightly.
flavor_text_entries.emerald:

positive and negative electricity from its
two antennae. It lives in depths beyond
sunlight’s reach.
